The paper discusses a high-level Python module for distributed machine learning inside TensorFlow, which integrates a wide range of state-of-art machine learning algorithms built on top of TensorFlow's low level APIs for small to large-scale supervised and unsupervised problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning algorithms for computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which makes these sub-categories likely as well. Finally, the mention of distributed machine learning (cs.DC) suggests that this sub-category is also a possibility.
